                            <comment id="14290569" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sat, 24 Jan 2015 12:12:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Underscore does appear to be valid in DNS&lt;br/&gt;
However it is not clear that such DNS entries are valid as host names, e.g. in URLs&lt;br/&gt;
RFCs references are needed here&lt;br/&gt;
Without proof that underscore is supported by the relevant RFC, I would be -1 to unconditionally allowing underscore in the RE used to check domain names.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14291740" author="britter" created="Mon, 26 Jan 2015 11:50:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fix has been reverted because of a veto on the dev ML:  &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/iqddbsdkmsrd2dqe&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/iqddbsdkmsrd2dqe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
